      "content": "i mean \"generally considered\" is a bit vague though. some studies show the ecological footprint of mining is way more intense than people admit, especially with toxic runoff and all that. shouldn't a scientific comparison give equal weight to those risks instead of just dismissing them as \"smaller\" compared to gas? isn't it a bit biased to just say wind is better because of carbon?",
